# ==============================================================================
# Notes for Contributors:
# ==============================================================================
#
# 1. Large files (>50MB) should NEVER be committed to git
#    - Use Git LFS: git lfs track "*.parquet"
#    - Or host externally and use download_metadata.py
#
# 2. Sample files (*.sample.parquet) are OK to commit if < 10MB
#
# 3. To check what will be committed:
#    git status --ignored
#    git ls-files --others --ignored --exclude-standard
#
# 4. To check file sizes before commit:
#    git ls-files | xargs ls -lh
#
# 5. If you accidentally committed large files:
#    git filter-branch --force --index-filter \
#      'git rm --cached --ignore-unmatch path/to/large/file' \
#      --prune-empty --tag-name-filter cat -- --all
#
# ==============================================================================
